com.mmm.cms.homehealth

Class GrouperDataManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mmm.cms.homehealth.GrouperDataManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataManagerIF, Initializable, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GrouperDataManager_V3312

    public class GrouperDataManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements DataManagerIF
    This class provides the ICD-9-CM Data management related to the Diagnosis codes, the NRS Diagnosis codes, the Diagnostic Groups, the Etiology Pairs, and the optional Payment code The information is loaded from text files. Refer to the loading methods for the file formats September 2012 - Replaced all HashMap field types with the more generic Map reference allowing for greater flexibility. Added the createDiagnosisCode() and createDiagnosticGroup() in order to allow extending classes to create their own implementation of each data type.
    Author:
    3M HIS Clinical & Economic Research for CMS Home Health
    See Also:
    throws IOException, FileNotFoundException,IOException, throws FileNotFoundException, IOException, Serialized Form

        Searchs the supplied diagnosis code table, codes, for the code value. If found, then the code is cloned to allow the calling module to change its attributes without effecting the original code, which remains in the same state as when it was loaded.

      • loadDiagnosisCodeBase

        protected void loadDiagnosisCodeBase(java.io.File file,
                                     java.util.Map<java.lang.String,DiagnosisCodeIF> codeHash,
                                     boolean isNrs)
                              throws java.io.IOException
        This is a consolidated/generic Diagnosis code loaded that requires the input file, and the hash map to put the codes into The data is loaded from a tab separated file with the format:
        • Diagnosis Code
        • Description
        • Diagnosis Group Number
        • Secondary only code indicated with M (without quotes) - can be blank
        • Diabetes related indicator - D = Diabetes, U = Diabetic Ulcer - can be blank
        Parameters:

        codeHash -
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
